---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
import demoVideo from '../../assets/portfolio/the_future_is_built_in_chicago.mp4';

const liveUrl = 'https://squareup.com/us/en/future/chi';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Square: The Future Is Built in Chicago"
  year="2021"
  tags={['Frontend', 'Animations', 'Experimentation', 'Ecommerce']}
  description="The Chicago edition of Square's multi-city Future Is Built Here campaign — a microsite celebrating local small businesses with custom animations and direct shopping."
  liveUrl={liveUrl}
  prevSlug="square-atlanta"
  prevTitle="The Future Is Built in Atlanta"
  nextSlug="square-podcast"
  nextTitle="Paying It Forward Podcast"
>

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Overview</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>
        The Chicago edition of the <strong>Future Is Built Here</strong> campaign followed the same structure as Atlanta — a city-specific microsite spotlighting local Square sellers — but with a distinct visual direction tailored to the city.
      </p>
      <p>
        Building the second city gave us the opportunity to refine and componentize the patterns developed in Atlanta, shipping faster with more polish.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cs-video">
    <video src={demoVideo} autoplay muted loop playsinline />
    <div class="cs-video-label">
      <span>squareup.com/us/en/future/chi</span>
      <a href={liveUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">View live ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="cs-divider" />

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Contribution</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>
        Frontend development across the full site — animations, responsive layout, and ecommerce integration. Refactored shared components from the Atlanta build to make the Chicago edition faster to ship and easier to maintain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="cs-divider" />

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Tech stack</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <ul class="cs-stack">
        <li>Svelte</li>
        <li>CSS Animations</li>
        <li>Square Ecommerce API</li>
        <li>Headless CMS</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>
